https://scm.sipfoundry.org/rep/sipX/branches/sipXconfig/replication
XCF-824 Allow for optional parameter (sip_domain) in topology.xml to support IMDB dataset replication to different SIP domain that the one sipX config is installed on.
IMDB replication: permission, credential and extension datasets now support injecting SIP domain name through DataSetGenerator.setSipDomain.
XCF-823 support for injecting additional mapping rules from external files 
file name can be specified in sipxconfig.properties.in file as mappingRule.externalRulesFileName parameter
XCF-809 replication.cgi is now used not just for replicating IMDB data but also for sending XML configuration files (mapping rules, fallback rules, authorization rules, orbits definition and emergency routing)
XCF-505 starting, stopping and restarting services works for multiple hosts, status of running services still only works for local host


